{"word":"ῥοδανός","slug":"ῥοδανός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n92577\" key=\"r(odano/s\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">ῥοδᾰνός</orth>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">ή</itype>, <itype lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"itype\">όν</itype>, perh. <sense id=\"n92577.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">wavering, flickering</tr_>, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">παρὰ ῥοδανὸν δονακῆα</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:18:576\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18.576</biblScope> </bibl> </cit>:—this is the reading of most codd., but ancient critics differed as to the form; <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Zenod.</author> </bibl> gave <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">διὰ ῥαδαλόν</foreign> (which he derived from <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">κραδαλόν</foreign>); the reading of Aristoph. and <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Aristarch.</author> </bibl> is uncertain, perh. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">παρὰ ῥαδινόν</foreign>, <abbr TEIform=\"abbr\">v.</abbr> Sch. ad loc.; cf. also <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥαδινός</foreign> (<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Apollon.\">Apollon.</a></author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Lex.\">Lex.</a></title_></bibl>, who reads <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">ῥαδινόν</foreign>, absurdly interprets as <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">λεπτόν, οἱονεὶ ῥαδονόν, παρὰ τὸ ῥᾳδίως δονεῖδθαι</foreign>).</sense> </entryFree>"}]}